h3. Workaround

Either of the following can be used:

* Alter the {{server.xml}} to serve only the required ciphers as per [Security tools report the default SSL Ciphers are too weak|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRAKB/Security+tools+report+the+default+SSL+Ciphers+are+too+weak].
* Host JIRA behind a reverse-proxy that will handle the serving of SSL as per [Integrating JIRA with Apache using SSL|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Integrating+JIRA+with+Apache+using+SSL].

